Package: BEAMR
Title: Bootstrap Evaluation of Association Matrices
Version: 1.1.0
Authors@R: c( person("Anna Eames", "Seffernick", ,
        "anna.seffernick@stjude.org", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
        comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-0848-4604")), person("Stanley",
        "Pounds", , "stanley.pounds@stjude.org", role = "aut"),
        person("Xueyuan", "Cao", , "xcao12@uthsc.edu", role = "aut") )
Description: A bootstrap-based approach to integrate multiple forms of
        high dimensional genomic data with multiple clinical endpoints.
        This method is used to find clinically meaningful groups of
        genomic features, such as genes or pathways. A manuscript
        describing this method is in preparation.
